skipping the piecies.
</p>

<p>
Neena saw  a dog,  barking along the  street under  a glittering
lamp. She looked up on the fifth floor. Nobody was there. “I bet
he had thrown the bottles at the dog”
</p>

<p>
“No he wouldn’t”  Deepak defeneded Rakesh, but he  knew that she
was right.
